spans.text: which from thy boundless Store , Out of thy self where all things lay , This beauteous Universe did call
vast empty Space , Where nothing all alone
our selves , and all these Blessings
which are from all the Dregs of Sense refined
Nothing's so high , nor yet so low , As to escape his Sight , He do's the Wants of all his Creatures know , And to relieve them
of all his Creatures know , And to relieve them
A Pleasure worthy that Almighty Mind
beg his Pardon , prostrate lie , And for Forgiveness to his Mercy fly :
Remember it's to him you owe your All
to mourn , And sighing to your Dust return
to mourn , And sighing to your Dust return
the rash Dictates of my Will
To its blessed Source , where constant Joys
To its blessed Source , where constant Joys are found , And where never ending Pleasures spread themselves around
